<item>
            <title>[SEC-810] User Lockout Manager</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-810</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my work, I needed in a few projects to provide a locking account mechanism.&lt;br/&gt;
When too many bad login attemps are done with bad password, the following attemps will be locked.&lt;br/&gt;
Having worked on Weblogic or OpenLDAP, i found those mechanisms in &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&quot;UserLockout Manager&quot; for Weblogic&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&quot;Ppolicy&quot; module for OpenLDAP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Common configuration options are :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;threshold (maximum of bad login attemps)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;duration of lock (automatic unlocking after a certain time)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;for in-memory systems (like SS), cache size for login attempts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Other Functionnalities needed :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;unlock users&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;determine if a user account is locked&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I find that such a module could be very useful for the community.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
